Description: 1971 Fender Stratocaster purchased used in 1980. Converted to 4-bolt neckplate by luthier John Carruthers (original 3-bolt plate with serial # included). Most recent fret job by Greg Bach. Chrome Schaller tuners. One original Pick-up - middle position (John Caruthers added copper shielding). Includes another non-functioning original pickup. Had "Natural Hippie Refin" when purchased. I sprayed it white ("cream" now, and funky in the back where I tried to protect/seal signatures).Used extensively on tour with Etta James, and Dick Clark's Good Old Rock 'n' Roll Show. Signed by Roy Orbison at a recording session for "Careless Heart" demo - released on "King of Hearts" album. Music and Sound Output Article documents asking Roy to sign it at the session. Soon after had Bo Diddley, Chuck Berry, Dick Clark and Del Shannon sign.When Roy passed I semi-retired guitar (no more signatures). Includes HSC with many Backstage passes: Etta James, House of Blues, Sting etc.Easy-playing '71 bullet truss rod neck straight and true dated "22 SEP 71B".Fender bridge with "Fender" saddles from "Ace Music" Santa Monica, CA.A vintage player's Stratocaster with a unique pedigree and history. See article featuring this guitar in Premier Guitar May 2013: https://www.premierguitar.com/articles/1971_Fender_Bullet_Stratocaster Video demonstrating this fully-functional, historic Fender Stratocaster: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8dwnaqfllBE . Shipping to lower 48 States only
Title: 1971 Fender Stratocaster signed by Roy Orbison, Del Shannon and more.
